 {"id":"cass_memory_system-4ua5","title":"[Impl] Add --robot Flag Convention (like cass)","description":"# Add --robot Flag Convention (like cass)

## Purpose
cass uses `--robot` as the primary flag for machine-readable output. We use `--json`. Should we add `--robot` as an alias for consistency across the agent tool ecosystem?

## Current State
- cass: `--robot` and `--json` both work
- cm: `--json` only

## Arguments For
- Consistency with cass (agents learn one pattern)
- `--robot` signals "I am an agent" not just "give me JSON"
- Can add robot-specific behaviors (suppress warnings, etc.)

## Arguments Against
- `--json` is already standard
- Adding aliases increases surface area
- Not strictly necessary

## Recommendation
Add `--robot` as an alias for `--json` plus:
- Suppress INFO-level stderr messages
- Ensure all output is parseable
- Add `cm robot-docs` command (like cass)

## Implementation
- Add --robot flag to all commands that have --json
- Make --robot = --json + quieter stderr
- Add cm robot-docs command with topics:
  - commands: all commands for agents
  - schemas: JSON output schemas
  - examples: copy-paste invocations
  - guide: quick-start for agents

## Deliverables
- [ ] --robot flag on all relevant commands
- [ ] cm robot-docs command
- [ ] Documentation of robot mode behavior","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-08T12:47:52.262-05:00","updated_at":"2025-12-08T13:13:38.167641-05:00","closed_at":"2025-12-08T13:13:38.167641-05:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"cass_memory_system-4ua5","depends_on_id":"cass_memory_system-2bnu","type":"blocks","created_at":"2025-12-08T12:48:46.681826-05:00","created_by":"daemon"}]}
